    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.22e"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">22e</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 24, 1957</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Now that I've read further in the Sterling letters I see that he did write "Lilith." It's on the agenda to talk about when I get back to Missouri. The study of you as a critic has simply <hi rend="underline">got</hi> to be made! The Sterling letters are perfect jewels--all of them. I have only a few more to read; it goes slowly because the microfilm lights make a three-hour stretch about the limit one can read--but it's a wonderful three hours!</p>
                
                <p>This is news: I've heard about Mrs. Ryskind. She is willing for me to see her father's papers, but she is a little concerned because they are personal in places. She is perfectly right not to turn them over to a perfect stranger; I am going to see her when we are in Los Angeles at Thanksgiving time, and work on them there. I should like to talk with her anyway, and I think when we meet she will not worry about my use of the letters. She wrote a very nice letter. (There are a <hi rend="underline">couple of hundred</hi> letters, Mrs. Ryskind says!)</p>
                
                <p>John Galen Howard's letters are not in the library at Berkeley, but the librarian gave me his son's address, and I'm writing to him.</p>
                
                <p>Mr. Russell sent me a copy of the 1941 Bookfellows Poetry Annual. It has the "Easter" poem in it. He also gave me some useful dates of Chicago speeches, and the citation on the Seymour tribute. So I'm progressing. The library <del>j</del><add>h</add>ere has all the periodicals like <hi rend="underline">Dial</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Munceys</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Outlook</hi> that I hoped would <del>h</del><add>b</add>e here.</p>
                
                <p>We saw in <hi rend="underline">Time</hi> that Dilliard has been demoted. What is happening at the <hi rend="caps">P-D</hi>--do you know? It sounds like upheaval. I think we're going to take the New York <hi rend="underline">Times</hi> and relax, if anyone can relax about a newspaper these days.</p>
                
                <p>I'll keep you up <del>y</del><add>t</add>o date on everything I find. Best regards to all the family.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>I see by the Missourian you are talking to the Law Wives in November. Will you write me about it afterwards?</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
